Oh my GOD their cinnamon rolls!! I genuinely think they are a contender for the best desserts I've ever tried in my life, which includes the 21 years I was not a vegan. They were so rich and moist, absolutely leagues better than the several vegan cinnamon rolls I've tried in recent months, and better than any nonvegan one I've tried. Perfect in every way, but the thing that blew me away the most was the bottom, it had this incredible layer of nearly hardened, chewy, caramelized cinnamon roll goodness.  Excellent food and pastries overall.  The best vegan cupcake I've ever had.  When my friend and I went vegan back in 2015 we tried their cupcakes back then, and we honestly thought they gave us the wrong food, it just didn't compute that this was a vegan cupcake, it was one of the best I've ever had, if not the best.  We contacted them and they said indeed it was!  Healthy options too, the Med Bowl is unbelievably satisfying. Lots of whole food selections on the menu, my only gripe would be the lack of 100% whole grain breads or wraps, at least the day I was there.  For comfort food I've recently tried the Crispy Chik'n sandwich, which was good but a little lacking in flavor punch. Maybe could use more or more prominent pickles, and more sauce. A kick of acid and spice maybe. Also the patty was a bit too thick.  Also recently tried the strawberry cupcake, spinach mozzarella biscuit (great), bacon cheese and kale danish (great), pecan coffee crumble (topping a little too dry but tasty), chocolate icing and marshmellow donut (I was told this had butter cream filling, but it was sadly just a light chocolate filling.  Pleased that it was fluffy dough rather than cake inside, but it was lacking in saltiness overall), marshmallow boston cream donught (pretty great), some kinda apple muffin with caraway seeds on top, pb&j bar.  For produce, they have a good selection, including black, and yellow/green striped (my favorite) figs in season.

If you want to surprise someone with a delicious bday cake DO NOT order vanilla raspberry cake with vanilla frosting. I’ve got this cake for my husbands birthday and it was a big disappointment. Why?  1. Filling: There was no raspberry flavor at all, there was no raspberry mousse layers in between the cakes. There is no cream or something similar to cream inside, just very very sweet frosting. 2. Cake: The cake wasn’t fluffy and light. It was more like a bread texture, not a sponge. There were a few red spots in the cake. Was it supposed to be the raspberry flavor?  Clementine Bakery why don’t you pack your vanilla raspberry cakes with raspberries instead of ultra sweet frosting? Raspberries are 100% vegan. Are you afraid the cake would get soggy? This cake is made to order, so it doesn’t sit in a fridge for days. I asked for extra raspberries on top of the cake, which was the only raspberry taste (I was charged 5$ extra for this).  I bake breads and vegan cakes myself, I know how hard it might be to get a light and fluffy spongey, perfectly moist cake, but it’s possible. If you’re not able to bake a good spongey cake, why don’t you compensate with  amazing fruit filling? Clementine Bakery owner: I would suggest you order this cake for yourself and try it and see what can be improved.  My husband didn’t like the cake at all and it ruined the bday vibe!

The entire menu is amazing, so if they happen to run out of some things before the end of day, don’t be afraid to try something else on their delicious menu! Cute spot with lots of light, plants and great vegan food. A fair amount of seating, a small queue at lunch and also outdoor seating options for nice days. The cauliflower curry was awesome and the portion huge. The flavours were really satisfying and it kept me full for hours on end - which doesn’t always happen when I eat vegan food. They ran out of chutney, so they substituted with cranberry sauce. I really wanted to try one of their sandwiches but they ran out of gluten free bread - but I suppose it gives me an excuse to go back. The double Chocolate cupcake was good because the frosting itself was delicious! As for the cake part it was a little dry and rice-y but not bad. Definitely would go back to try more! For what it was, the prices are definitely very reasonable too :)

I placed an order last night for a cake for Father's Day for a Dad I haven't had the opportunity to see for over a year. I called today to find out how I could pay for said cake being that I never got the followup call after the confirmation email. No biggie.  I get a well worn sounding woman on the phone who seemed slightly annoyed prior to picking up the phone, only to be told that "there is no more space" for orders after explaining that I had placed an order online and wanted to pay. Okay? Don't call the people who placed orders and let them know their order isn't valid so they can go elsewhere for business instead of waiting for a call that wouldn't come, that makes sense. I think you should take the option down or put up a banner that says you are no longer taking orders, so people won't be ordering thinking they can do something nice for someone in their lives, when they obviously can't.  I didn't want to beg, but I explained my situation asking if there was anything we can do and she said "come into the store" right after I told her I'm placing the order from halfway across the world :[ womp womp womp. Guess that's how it is when you run your own business.  Just a heads up for people trying to get vegan goodies out to the loved ones in their lives; either order way in advance or don't order at all, that seems to be how things worked for my first experience.
